description:
People have an average diuresis of 50 ml/h on the ground. When immersed, this diuresis increases about 7 times, i.e. it becomes about 350 ml/h. If the person feels cold, this diuresis increases even further. In these circumstances, it is not uncommon for a diver to lose in 5 hours of diving between 1500 and 2000 ml of water through diuresis. Electrolytes such as sodium, potassium, magnesium, and phosphates are lost through diuresis and perspiration. Restoring fluids in these long duration dives is mandatory. Drinking large amounts of fluids immediately before diving as a way of hydrating is not very effective, since almost all the liquid drank is eliminated in the first hours, and the distention of the stomach from excessive liquid may cause gastroesophageal reflux with epigastric burning and acid regurgitation in the mouth.
Immersed hydration should be gradual, similar to what athletes do. Every hour, an amount of around 300 ml seems reasonable, since in addition to avoiding the disadvantages cited above, the diver remains adequately hydrated with a slightly positive hydric balance, which is beneficial for diving.


O ser humano apresenta, em média, 50 ml/h de diurese no ambiente terrestre. Quando submerso, a diurese aumenta algo em torno de sete vezes, ou seja, passa para 350 ml/h. Caso sinta frio, há ainda um incremento na diurese. Não é incomum sob tais circunstâncias, o mergulhador perder em 5 horas de mergulho entre 1500 e 2000 ml de água por essa via. Eletrólitos, tais como sódio, potássio, magnésio e fosfatos, são perdidos por meio da diurese e da perspiração.
A reposição de fluidos nos mergulhos de longa duração é mandatória. A ingestão de grandes quantidades de fluidos imediatamente antes do mergulho, como forma de hidratação não surte muito efeito, pois quase todo líquido ingerido é eliminado nas primeiras horas e a distensão do estômago pelo excesso de líquido pode provocar refluxo gastroesofágico com queimor epigástrico, assim como regurgitação ácida na boca.
A hidratação submersa deve ser gradual, à semelhança do que os atletas fazem. De hora em hora, a ingestão de quantidades em torno de 300 ml parece ser algo razoável, pois, além de evitar os inconvenientes supracitados, mantém o mergulhador adequadamente hidratado com um balanço hídrico levemente positivo, o que é benéfico para o mergulho.
title: Hydration During the Dive

description:
Holoska
Night
Dark Moray

The second Werehog boss in the game is a bit more complicated than the Dark Gaia Phoenix...or not. I don't actually know. They're all so simple when I remembered their patterns entirely. I do remember taking a while to figure out what needs to be done, unlike the Dark Gaia Phoenix, so its definitely a step up.

The Dark Moray is a stationary boss, but somehow, it has control of a force field creating device that Sonic needs to disable before he can get to it. There are three main phases to the battle corresponding to the three pimples or cysts or whatever they are; each time Sonic pops one, the Dark Moray knocks Sonic back to the outer ring and turns the force field back on. Sonic will need to disable the machine again. Also, the Nightmares and Deep Nightmares you see here are just for distraction. You can pretty much ignore them.

For the third phase, you're supposed to freeze Dark Moray when it slams itself against the floor, then go on top and attack the lump on its back right below its head. It wasn't getting itself in the proper position, so I just slowly wore away its health.

The way there's a small outpost of highly advanced technology in a the middle of a bunch of ice floating over the ocean reminds me of Metroid...

Requested by phantom1053
title: Sonic Unleashed - Wii - Dark Moray

depending on how long you've been subbed to me, you may not know about these flings we do at my yard, basically we all gallop after someone on a lead horse around the farm over the hunt jumps (it is so much fun.)

We always jump this hedge, and the pictures at the begining show the three times i've attempted it ahaaa :L first he walked through, then i fell off last october, then yesterday i fell off AGAIN exactly the same way! THEN WE FINALLY JUMPED IT!!!!

I know that we are both jumping it with a certain amount of style ;) but no lie this is one huge freaking hedge, i'm so happy!!! Thank you Milly and Paddy (the yellow pony who is usually in my videos) for leading us over without a lead :O Paddy's a legend :D

And then i nearly fell off the other side as well but somehow managed the get back in the saddle, idk how :L 'like' for stickability factor?! ;) AND FOR MY AMAZING LITTLE COB

Thank you to my dad for taking these incredible pictures! will have the full fling video up at some point 

-emily and taffy xxxxxx

description:
Wound management is one of the cornerstones of good nursing care. Effective wound care extends far beyond the application of the wound dressing. Nurses and nursing assistants may be required to assess, plan, implement and evaluate wound care. In order to fulfil these roles, it's critical to have an understanding of the several basic procedures involved in wound care. 

In this program we examine skin anatomy, the classification of wounds, wound procedures, wound dressings, and documentation. Knowledge in each of these areas will allow nurses and nursing assistants to make well informed decisions about wound care and ultimately play an active part in promoting wound healing.

To find out more about Wound Management: A Nurse's Guide visit:
http://www.vea.com.au

WOUND1
title: Wound Management: A Nurse's Guide

description:
Hanatarash was a noise unit from Osaka, founded in 1983 by Yamatsuka Eye. ハナタラシ (洟垂らし) literally means "sniveler", ie a person with a snotty or runny nose. Others translate it at "Snot-nosed".

Hanatarash are infamous for their extremely dangerous live shows consisting entirely of on-stage destruction and utter disregard for anyone's safety. The most notorious incident involved Yamatsuka throwing junk around with a backhoe inside a venue. On another occasion, he inflicted a deep wound on his leg with an electrical saw, but carried on with the show. A dead cat is also known to have been cut in half during a show. The band once caused so much damage to a live house in Kyoto that it was forced to close.

At a 1985 gig in Tokyo's Superloft, Hanatarash had the audience fill out forms relieving the band of responsibility for any possible bodily harm caused by the performance. The show stopped just as Yamatsuka was about to throw a lit molotov cocktail onto the stage, which was gasoline-drenched from a barrel. The performance cost the venue ¥600,000 ($6000) in repair costs.

Soon unable to be allowed to play anywhere, Yamatsuka went on to form Ultra Freak Out Or Die and Boredoms, among countless other projects. The 1990s saw Hanatarash resurface with some releases and performances, sans on-stage mayhem.

"4: AIDS-a-Delic" is one of thier releases and the reason why I say that is because this album was either released in 1996 or 1994. I have used the alternative cover of this album because the original one has female nipples on it and youtube fears those. Go to this link for more info. http://www.discogs.com/Hanatarash-4/release/332020
title: Hanatarash - My Tooth is Sore Diamond
